ther to mervaile more, either that hee in that mistie time could see so clearly, or that wee in this cleare age, goe so stumblingly after him." The text can be found at <a href="http://www.uoregon.edu/~rbear/defence.html" class="external text external" id="mwBhs">uoregon.edu</a></span></li><li id="cite_note-72"><a href="Geoffrey_Chaucer#cite_ref-72" id="mwBhw"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwBh0">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-72" class="mw-reference-text">Richard Utz, "Chaucer among the Victorians", <i id="mwBh4">Oxford Handbook of Victorian Medievalism</i>, ed. Joanna Parker and Corinna Wagner (Oxford: OUP, 2020): pp. 189-201.</span></li><li id="cite_note-73"><a href="Geoffrey_Chaucer#cite_ref-73" id="mwBh8"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwBiA">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-73" class="mw-reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFBesserman2006" class="citation book cs1">Besserman, Lawrence (2006). <a href="https://www.academia.edu/20310557" class="external text external" id="mwBiI"><i id="mwBiM">The Chaucer Review</i></a>. Penn State University Press. pp.<span id="mwBiQ">&nbsp;</span>100–103.</cite></span></li><li id="cite_note-74"><a href="Geoffrey_Chaucer#cite_ref-74" id="mwBiY"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwBic">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-74" class="mw-reference-text">Benson, Larry, <i id="mwBig">The Riverside Chaucer</i> (Boston: Houghton Mifflin, 1987), p. 1118.</span></li><li id="cite_note-75"><a href="Geoffrey_Chaucer#cite_ref-75" id="mwBik"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwBio">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-75" class="mw-reference-text">Potter, Russell A., "Chaucer and the Authority of Language: The Politics and Poetics of the Vernacular in Late Medieval England", <i id="mwBis">Assays</i> VI (Carnegie-Mellon Press, 1991), p. 91.</span></li><li id="cite_note-76"><a href="Geoffrey_Chaucer#cite_ref-76" id="mwBiw"><span class="mw-linkback-text" id="mwBi0">↑ </s